{
  "stem": "9730.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But you had to have proof that you had all the necessary exit visas from the other countries concerned, which meant France and Spain and sometimes Portugal, because that's how they would have left, had they been able to leave.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And also, you had to show ships' reservations, and very often those ships would sail.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- and my parents hadn't even been asked to appear before the American consul-- consul in Marseille.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So to get that timing right and to always be ready with reservations, it was just one frustration after another.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so, as I was saying, the-- last-- this went on until May of '42.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And eventually, later in the-- in the fall of '42, before I went in the army, some of the letters that I had sent to them came back saying, 'Address Unknown,' 'Left No Forwarding Address.' And-- so we knew that we could fear the worst, although we didn't know, of course, exactly what had happened.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I was well aware of, you know, what I probably had to contend with.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I believe you asked me a question about whether I was still in touch with my parents once I was in the army.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The answer to that is no.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the biggest irony of all is that-- that in November, after I was in the army in November of '42, we received word from the State Department that they had advised their consulate in Marseille to grant visas to my parents.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The only irony of that was that my parents had been deported to Auschwitz two months earlier, as we found out after the war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I shipped out right after the invasion started, June 6.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went to a staging area in-- in the south of England.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
